A lesson I thought I learned years ago (@frew iykyk)…yet I have found myself again living a life dictated by numbers…numbers of people deciding who I am based off of my social media persona; numbers of gaslights when attempting to confront abuse; numbers of comments on my body being too much yet not enough; numbers of times random humans tap the screen; numbers of let downs from those who present with false intentions; numbers of times we exchange performative connection for real human connection. While the type and severity has changed, I have struggled with addiction for the majority of my life. It is poignantly clear that social media has become another coping mechanism for me (and many others) to try and claim control over something. In reality I am losing time. In reality I am enabling a sexist culture that caters to the whims of men. TLDR I will be moving away from this app for a while. Take care my Instagram people and a reminder that the rabbit hole doesn’t only go one way…💛
